  "source_id": "diverticulitis",
  "name": "Diverticulitis - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying all diverticulitis patients using Condition (diverticulitis dx) + MedicationRequest (cipro/metro). Path C patients have cipro+metro without diverticulitis dx (likely treated empirically for intra-abdominal infection or unconfirmed UTI/IAI).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete diverticulitis patient population for a colorectal quality initiative. Some patients have a coded diverticulitis diagnosis. Others were prescribed ciprofloxacin and metronidazole empirically for suspected intra-abdominal infection without ever getting a formal diverticulitis diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and antibiotic medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with diverticulitis or on cipro/metro.",
    "broad": "Find all diverticulitis patients — by diagnosis or by ciprofloxacin/metronidazole antibiotic regimen. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|307496006 — diverticulitis dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|2551,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|6922 — cipro+metro. Union the patient IDs."
  },
